description:
The objectives of this course are to introduce students to the concepts, methods and techniques of business analytics. Students will gain the requisite skills to perform analytics in a real life business scenarios through workshops and assignments using tools. Topics included in the course are:
• Introduction to Business Analytics (NEW);
• Business Intelligence fundamentals (NEW);
• Exploratory data analysis and visualization;
• Segmentation and clustering;
• Market basket analysis;
• Advanced modelling using decision trees, rule induction, regression, neural networks;
• Data mining for CRM and market planning;
• Data mining tools.
This course is highly appropriate for all professional workers who must process and analyze large amounts of data for corporate decision making.
